<p>Hey there! üëã I‚Äôm <strong><em>Jagadeesh Mummana</em></strong>, and this is my little corner of the internet where I‚Äôll be sharing all things robotics, AI, and the random tech experiments I get into.</p>]]></description>
      <content:encoded>&lt;![CDATA[<!-- ##### Welcome to My Blog! üöÄ   -->
<p>Hey there! üëã I‚Äôm <strong><em>Jagadeesh Mummana</em></strong>, and this is my little corner of the internet where I‚Äôll be sharing all things robotics, AI, and the random tech experiments I get into.</p>
<p>If you‚Äôre into building cool stuff, tinkering with microcontrollers, or just figuring out how things work, you‚Äôre in the right place. I‚Äôve been into this world of electronics and automation for a while now, and I thought it was about time I started documenting the chaos.</p>
<hr>
<h5 id="why-start-a-blog">Why Start a Blog?</h5>
<p>Honestly? Because I realized I‚Äôve been building all these projects, learning so much along the way, but barely writing any of it down. Most of my work is scattered across random folders on my laptop, and that‚Äôs not helping anyone‚Äînot even me.</p>
<p>So, this blog is my way of organizing my thoughts, sharing what I know, and hopefully connecting with people who are just as passionate about tech as I am. Plus, I figured committing to a weekly blog post (every <strong><em>Friday</em></strong>, to keep myself accountable) might force me to stay consistent.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>My motto?</strong> &ldquo;Knowledge grows best when shared.&rdquo;</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<h5 id="who-am-i">Who Am I?</h5>
<p>I‚Äôm currently a sophomore at <strong>NIT Calicut</strong>, studying <strong>Electronics and Communication Engineering</strong>, with a minor in <strong>Robotics and Automation</strong>.</p>
<p>If I had to describe myself, I‚Äôd say I‚Äôm someone who loves building things, breaking things (not always on purpose!), and figuring out how stuff works. My favorite projects are the ones where software meets hardware‚Äîit‚Äôs where the real magic happens.</p>
